Olusegun Adetoro, father of two-year-old Esther Fiyinfoluwa Adetoro, is seeking N6m to treat her of a heart disease (tetralogy of fallot). He is appealing to the general public to help him raise the cash to pay for surgery. Adetoro, who spoke with journalists in Akure, said his daughter was diagnosed with the disease in January, 2020. A medical report signed by Dr. A.D. Adenle, said her left and right atriums are dilated.   Three women seek N10m for ‘illegal debits’     May a greedy soul not be our next president     Enforcement of okada ban begins in Lagos   The report reads in parts, “The left ventricular outlook tract is unobstructed and the flow is laminar. The aortic valve is tri-leaflet with no evidence of significant stenosis or regurgitation. The left and right coronary arteries were clearly identified following the normal course.” He said the University of Medical Sciences Teaching Hospital Complex, Akure, Ondo State, demanded N6m for surgery. The report, signed by Dr. O.A. Olubosede, said the “child is diagnosed with a congenital heart disease (Tetralogy of Fallot). She will need about N6 million for the surgery to correct the defect. Adetoro said he has spent a fortune to sustain the child despite their poor financial status. He could be reached on 08068702540. His account details are: Adetoro Cornelius Olusegun, Union Bank, 0111057750.